  "response": "Here are key steps to make your website SEO-friendly:\n\n1. Technical SEO\n- Ensure mobile responsiveness\n- Improve website loading speed\n- Create a clear site structure\n- Use SSL certificate\n- Submit XML sitemap to search engines\n\n2. On-Page SEO\n- Use relevant keywords naturally\n- Create unique, high-quality content\n- Optimize title tags and meta descriptions\n- Use header tags (H1, H2, etc.)\n- Include alt text for images\n- Create internal links\n- Use descriptive URLs\n\n3. Content Strategy\n- Publish high-quality, original content\n- Target long-tail keywords\n- Update content regularly\n- Create comprehensive, in-depth articles\n- Answer user questions\n\n4. Performance Optimization\n- Compress images\n- Minimize code\n- Use browser caching\n- Reduce server response time\n\n5. Additional Tactics\n- Build quality backlinks\n- Use Google Search Console\n- Enable rich snippets\n- Create a Google My Business profile\n- Use social media sharing\n\n6. Technical Best Practices\n- Implement schema markup\n- Ensure crawlability\n- Remove duplicate content\n- Use canonical tags\n\nRemember, SEO is an ongoing process requiring consistent effort and adaptation to search engine algorithms.",
